For a geometric progression, the ratio of any two terms must be the same. Let $a$ be the ratio.  Then, we have \begin{align*}
\arcsin (\sin 2 \alpha) &= a \arcsin (\sin \alpha), \\
\arcsin (\sin 7 \alpha) &= a^2 \arcsin (\sin \alpha), \\
\arcsin (\sin t \alpha) &= a^3 \arcsin (\sin \alpha).
\end{align*}

